<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,712,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,712,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
─The yellow flowers with prominent dark red blotches on the posterior petals are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Harvey (1860: 264)" authorityName="Harvey" authorityPageNumber="264" authorityYear="1860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moniliforme">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">P. moniliforme</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Harvey, W. H." box="[279,500,748,775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" pagination="259 - 308" refId="ref5691" refString="Harvey, W. H. (1860) Geraniaceae. In: Harvey, W. H. &amp; Sonder, O. W. (Eds.) Flora Capensis. Vol. 1. Hodges, Smith &amp; Co, Dublin, pp. 259 - 308." type="book chapter" year="1860">Harvey (1860: 264)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="E. M. Marais (2000: 190)" authorityName="E. M. Marais" authorityPageNumber="190" authorityYear="2000" box="[553,967,748,774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vinaceum">
<emphasis box="[553,687,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">P. vinaceum</emphasis>
E.M. 
<bibRefCitation author="Marais, E. M." box="[744,967,748,774]" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" pagination="29" refId="ref6185" refString="Marais, E. M. (2000) Since the Ph. D thesis: Marais, E. M. (1994), Taxonomic studies in Pelargonium, section Hoarea (Geraniaceae). Ph. D. thesis, University of Stellenbosch, was reprinted and distributed by the Geraniaceae Group (England) in 2000, the name Pelargonium vinaceum E. M. Marais is considered effectively published from March 2000 (Article 29 of the International Code of Botanical Nomenclature, Greuter et al. 1994)." type="journal article" year="2000">Marais (2000: 190)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. M. Marais &amp; A. le Roux" authorityYear="2021" box="[1020,1254,748,774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hammansbergense">
<emphasis box="[1020,1254,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">P. hammansbergense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in that the erect to patent leaves are simple to pinnately divided, the scape branched, and the anterior stamens more or less the same length as the sepals. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harvey" authorityYear="1860" box="[499,665,820,846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="moniliforme">
<emphasis box="[499,665,820,846]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">P. moniliforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. M. Marais" authorityYear="2000" box="[721,857,821,846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vinaceum">
<emphasis box="[721,857,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="94">P. vinaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have simple to ternate, prostrate leaves, unbranched scapes and the anterior stamens always longer than the sepals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
